<p><b>What is the Bitcoin halving and how does it affect altcoins?</b></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The Bitcoin halving, which occurs approximately every four years, is expected to happen sometime this April. This event has implications for both the Bitcoin market and the broader cryptocurrency ecosystem, including altcoins. The halving event reduces the rate at which new Bitcoins are created, cutting the rewards for miners in half. While it is challenging to determine the exact impact the Bitcoin halving will have on the crypto landscape, some analysts believe the halving can generate increased attention on altcoins and influence market dynamics.</span></p>
<p><b>Why is the crypto market shifting towards Altcoins?</b></p>
